# Spec-Driven Development Rule

- For new features or significant changes, check if a spec exists in `docs/specs/` or create one using the template at `docs/specs/README.md`
- Implement features following spec requirements (REQ-F-001, etc.) and reference them in code comments and commit messages
- Update spec status from "Draft" to "Implemented" when complete
- Write specs for: new features/agents/tools, API changes, significant refactoring
- Skip specs for: bug fixes, docs-only changes, trivial cleanup, dependency updates
